15112	The Association of White Metals has decided to publish a daily tin price here in French francs per 100 kilos the French Federation of Non-Ferrous Metals said The price quoted for the first time yesterday was introduced as the lack of tin quotes was causing problems for some French companies a spokesman for the non-ferrous metals association said Todays price was set at 4776 francs per 100 kilos and Tuesdays at 4790 The International Chamber of Commerce stopped publishing a tin price after the London Metal Exchange LME stopped tin trading on October 24 1985 The Association has tested the basis it uses to calculate a French franc price over the last few months to ensure it was reliable the spokesman said The French franc price is pre-tax for specified quality a minimum 999 pct purity at a French port or border railway station and a minimum delivery of 10 tonnes The French Federation of Non-Ferrous Metals groups various metal associations including the Association of White Metals
